South African Police Arrest 89 Over Service Delivery Protests, Sapa Says

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-02-16T06:28:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/south-african-police-arrest-89-over-service-delivery-protests-sapa-says.html
South African police arrested 89
people after violent protests over a lack of government services
and jobs in Mpumalanga province, South African Press Association
said, citing a police spokeswoman.  The Wesselton protesters were arrested on public violence
charges, Captain Carla Prinsloo said, according to the
Johannesburg-based news agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
